OL,3,CHillsborough Law Independent Advocate
OL,4,C'needs more powers'
OL,6,F"A version of the independent public
OL,7,Fadvocate was enacted by the previous
OL,8,FGovernment towards the end of its time
OL,9,Fin office, and an appointment to the
OL,10,Foffice has been made by the current
OL,11,FGovernment.
OL,13,F"However, I do not believe that she
OL,14,Fhas sufficient powers or sufficient
OL,15,Fresource to do the job my Bill
OL,16,Fenvisaged. I may well try to explore
OL,17,Fin committee, where it is in order,
OL,18,Fwhat can be done about that.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOU
